revision.text:
'''Alienated [[Real property|land]]''' is that which has been acquired from customary landowners by Government, either for its own use or private development requiring a mortgage or other forms of guarantees. The term refers historically to the appropriation of [[customary land]] by European [[colonialism|colonial powers]]. Land was alienated in all colonies.
